      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is the clinically relevant metric for blood pump hemolysis assessment per FDA guidance and ASTM F1841. The relative hemolysis index (RH < 1) is the regulatory acceptance criterion. The CFD model directly computes the scalar transport field used to evaluate the power-law hemolysis model, producing NIH as a direct model output. The QoI is thus directly computed, not inferred from surrogate quantities.",
