      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model is selected based on its established performance for rotating machinery and adverse pressure gradient flows. The power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) is the standard model for CFD hemolysis prediction in blood pumps, with validation evidence in the literature for similar devices. Model form uncertainty is acknowledged and bounded by the validation comparison; residual model form error is within the validation uncertainty interval.",
