      "rationale": "A parameter equivalency table maps each experimental test condition to the corresponding CFD boundary condition, documenting any differences and their estimated impact on QoI. Key equivalency items: (1) experimental fluid temperature controlled to 37±0.5 °C versus CFD isothermal assumption — impact on viscosity estimated at <1%; (2) experimental inlet turbulence intensity measured at 8% versus CFD inlet specification of 8% — exact match; (3) pump rotational speed controlled to ±5 RPM in experiments versus exact specification in CFD — impact on NIH estimated at <0.5%.",
